yacx

Class Executor

  • java.lang.Object
    • yacx.Executor

  • public class Executor
extends java.lang.Object
    Class for initialization (load native library) and easily execute CUDA kernels.
    Before using other classes in this package it is necessary to load the native library.

      • benchmark

        public static Executor.BenchmarkResult benchmark(java.lang.String kernelString,
                                                 java.lang.String kernelName,
                                                 Options options,
                                                 Device device,
                                                 int numberExecutions,
                                                 Executor.KernelArgCreator creator,
                                                 long... dataSizesBytes)
        Benchmark a CUDA kernel.
        Parameters:
        kernelString - string containing the CUDA kernelcode
        kernelName - name of the kernel
        options - options for the nvtrc compiler
        device - device on which the benchmark-test should be executed
        numberExecutions - number of executions for the kernel
        creator - KernelArgCreator for creating KernelArgs for the kernel for every data size
        dataSizesBytes - data sizes of the kernel arguments, which should be tested, in bytes
        Returns:
        result of benchmark-test

      • benchmark

        public static Executor.BenchmarkResult benchmark(java.lang.String kernelString,
                                                 java.lang.String kernelName,
                                                 Options options,
                                                 Device device,
                                                 java.lang.String[] templateParameter,
                                                 int numberExecutions,
                                                 Executor.KernelArgCreator creator,
                                                 long... dataSizesBytes)
        Benchmark a CUDA kernel.
        Parameters:
        kernelString - string containing the CUDA kernelcode
        kernelName - name of the kernel
        options - options for the nvtrc compiler
        device - device on which the benchmark-test should be executed
        templateParameter - array of templateParameters or an empty array if the kernel do not contains template parameters
        numberExecutions - number of executions for the kernel for every data size
        creator - KernelArgCreator for creating KernelArgs for the kernel
        dataSizesBytes - data sizes of the kernel arguments, which should be tested, in bytes
        Returns:
        result of benchmark-test
